{"title_page": "Rumyancho Goranov", "text_new": "{{short description|Bulgarian footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name            = Rumyancho Goranov\n| image            =  Rumyancho Goranov 1974.jpg\n| caption = Rumyancho Goranov in 1974\n| fullname         = Rumyancho Goranov Radev \n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1950|3|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Pleven]], [[Bulgaria]]\n| height           = \n| position         = [[Goalkeeper (football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub      = \n| years1           = 1967\u20131970 | clubs1  = [[PFC Spartak Pleven|Spartak Pleven]]   | caps1 = 14  | goals1 = 0\n| years2           = 1970\u20131971 | clubs2  = [[PFC Levski Sofia|Levski Sofia]]       | caps2 = 2   | goals2 = 0\n| years3           = 1971\u20131982 | clubs3  = [[PFC Lokomotiv Sofia|Lokomotiv Sofia]] | caps3 = 245 | goals3 = 0\n| years4           = 1982\u20131984 | clubs4  = [[APOEL FC|APOEL]]                      | caps4 =     | goals4 = \n| years5           = 1984\u20131986 | clubs5  = [[Aris Limassol F.C.|Aris Limassol]]    | caps5 =     | goals5 = \n| years6           = 1986\u20131988 | clubs6  = [[Olympiakos Nicosia]]\n| years7           = 1988\u20131989 |  \nclubs7  =  [[Mosta FC]] | caps7 = 14| goals7 = 1              | caps6 =     | goals6 = \n| nationalyears1 = 1971\u20131979\n| nationalteam1 = [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 34\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Rumyancho Goranov Radev''' ({{Lang-bg|\u0420\u0443\u043c\u044f\u043d\u0447\u043e \u0413\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u0420\u0430\u0434\u0435\u0432}}; 17 March 1950) is a former [[Bulgaria]]n [[football (soccer)|football]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=50147/index.html Goranov Statistics at FIFA World Cup]  fifa.com</ref>\n\nHe played mostly for [[PFC Lokomotiv Sofia|Lokomotiv Sofia]]. With [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgarian national team]] he participated at [[1974 FIFA World Cup]]. He gained 34 caps for Bulgaria.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/bulg-recintlp.html Bulgaria \u2013 Record International Players] rsssf.com</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n* '''[[PFC Lokomotiv Sofia|Lokomotiv Sofia]]'''\n**[[A PFG]]:\n***Winner: [[1977\u201378 A PFG|1977\u201378]]\n**[[Bulgarian Cup]]:\n***Winner: 1981\u201382\n* '''[[PFC Levski Sofia|Levski Sofia]]'''\n**[[Bulgarian Cup]]:\n***Winner: 1970\u201371\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://en.levskisofia.info/player/rumyancho-goranov/ Profile at LevskiSofia.info]\n\n{{Bulgarian Footballer of the Year}}\n{{Bulgaria Squad 1974 World Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Goranov, Rumyancho}}\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian footballers]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:1974 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Bulgaria international footballers]]\n[[Category:PFC Spartak Pleven players]]\n[[Category:PFC Levski Sofia players]]\n[[Category:FC Lokomotiv 1929 Sofia players]]\n[[Category:First Professional Football League (Bulgaria) players]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Pleven]]\n[[Category:APOEL FC players]]\n[[Category:Aris Limassol FC players]]\n[[Category:Olympiakos Nicosia players]]\n[[Category:Cypriot First Division players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Cyprus]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian expatriate sportspeople in Cyprus]]\n\n\n{{Bulgaria-footy-goalkeeper-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name            = Rumyancho Goranov\n| image            =  Rumyancho Goranov 1974.jpg\n| caption = Rumyancho Goranov in 1974\n| fullname         = Rumyancho Goranov Radev \n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1950|3|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Pleven]], [[Bulgaria]]\n| height           = \n| position         = [[Goalkeeper (football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub      = \n| years1           = 1